Description: Narrow board of wood from the end of a wooden coffin; paint on plaster(worn); ends mitred for joins and dowel-hol;es present. The exterior bears a line of hieroglyphic text in green on a yellow ground. Interior surface covered by cream plaster. Left end damaged.
Excavator/field collector: Excavated by: Dr David George Hogarth
Bibliographic references: Zitman 2010 / The necropolis of Assiut: a case study of local Egyptian funerary culture from the Old Kingdom to the end of the Middle Kingdom (II, 131, 215)
